"title": "8432: fasting, practice of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8432",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Although fasting is a negative practice, it is not an end in itself but is to be undertaken for a positive purpose.</p>\n<h2>Fasting is not an end in itself</h2>\n<h3>Fasting as empty ritual is condemned</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer14:11-Jer14:12\">JER 14:11–14:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:1-Isa58:7\">ISA 58:1–58:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech7:4-Zech7:7\">ZEC 7:4–7:7</a></p>\n<h3>Fasting as mere show is condemned</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:16-Matt6:18\">MAT 6:16–6:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:14-Matt9:15\">MAT 9:14–9:15</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:18-Mark2:20\">MRK 2:18–2:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:33-Luke5:35\">LUK 5:33–5:35</a> <em>Jesus Christ repudiated fasting for its own sake whilst granting that there is a time and a place for it.</em></p>\n<h3>Fasting imposed for false motives</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam14:24-1Sam14:30\">1SA 14:24–14:30</a></p>\n<h2>Attitudes appropriate to fasting</h2>\n<h3>Humility</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:13\">PSA 35:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:27-1Kgs21:29\">1KI 21:27–21:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra8:21\">EZR 8:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:10\">PSA 69:10</a></p>\n<h3>Repentance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam7:6\">1SA 7:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:1-Neh9:3\">NEH 9:1–9:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:13-Joel1:14\">JOL 1:13–1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:12-Joel2:15\">JOL 2:12–2:15</a></p>\n<h2>Fasting and prayer</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:4\">NEH 1:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra8:21-Ezra8:23\">EZR 8:21–8:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:13\">PSA 35:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:3\">DAN 9:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:20\">MAT 17:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:29\">MRK 9:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:37\">LUK 2:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:33\">LUK 5:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:3\">ACT 13:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:23\">ACT 14:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:3-1Cor7:5\">1CO 7:3–7:5</a> <em>The motivation here is similar to that in abstaining from food.</em></p>\n<h2>Fasting and worship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:2\">ACT 13:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:37\">LUK 2:37</a></p>",
